registry.comment: ============================================================= <FILEENTITIES> tag sets up entity references which can be used in the stylesheets' <FILEREF> and <DSSSL> tags. For example: <refname>Foo</refname> <filename> <d>$approot$</d> <d>toolbox</d> <d>rptgen</d> <d>private</d> <f>jadechunker.dsl</f> </filename>

============================================================= <VARIABLES> tag - references built-in variables in the stylesheet. Many stylesheet authors allow variables to be defined using (define %variable-name% "value") in the customization layer. For a complete list of variable parameters see dbparam.dsl in the print or HTML stylesheets.

<ID> tag is used as a unique identifier to the stylesheet. Names may change, but ID's should not. Lists of stylesheets are sorted by ID, not name. The "default" sheet begins with a "!" since it is the first keyboard character.
